# Tailwind CSS guidelines

- Use Tailwind classes directly in JSX; avoid inline styles.
- Prefer common color scales: `slate/gray/zinc` for neutrals; brand accent `indigo` by default; `rose` for destructive; `emerald` for success; `amber` for warnings.
- Support dark mode with `dark:` variants for backgrounds, text, borders, and focus states.
- Responsive first: use `sm / md / lg / xl / 2xl` breakpoints; design web-first.
- Use consistent spacing (`px-`, `py-`, `gap-`, `space-*`) and radius (`rounded-*`).
- Include accessible focus styles: `focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-indigo-500` (and dark variants as needed).
- Prefer semantic utilities (`text-sm`, `font-medium`, `leading-6`) over arbitrary values.
- Group stateful variants consistently: `disabled:`, `aria-checked:`, `data-[state=...]` when applicable.
